# Implementation Core Rules

1. At the start of each new session, read `.cursor/memories/roadmap.md` and provide status in this order:
   - where we are at
   - what we need to implement next
   - what we just implemented
2. After the status briefing, collaborate with the user on detailed module execution planning before coding non-trivial work.
3. Keep changes focused and minimal. Avoid broad refactors unless required by active roadmap scope.
4. Reuse existing project patterns/components before adding new abstractions.
5. Do not silently change architecture decisions in the roadmap; document any justified deviation.
6. Validate behavior after edits, but default to ephemeral checks:
   - preferred: CLI runs, targeted commands, one-off temporary scripts
   - avoid: creating persisted test files unless explicitly requested by user
7. If validation is incomplete, clearly report what was not verified and why.
